{"type":"text","timestamp":1780728859583,"sessionID":"ses_1644b0d23ffeX4h16ioztT6XB0","part":{"id":"prt_e9bb5f68f001ARul0jY9RfwXDa","messageID":"msg_e9bb5e0c40015pyQypwsTnfEFA","sessionID":"ses_1644b0d23ffeX4h16ioztT6XB0","type":"text","text":"For idempotency, I’m checking both the HTTP middleware and the storage-side claim/complete paths, because the race behavior is defined by their combination.","time":{"start":1780728854159,"end":1780728859579},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04e51764e092a4a7016a23c41628588191b171e9e900b86c28","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728859626,"sessionID":"ses_1644b0d23ffeX4h16ioztT6XB0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_fg73fTr5wz1vcXg1HiMzBK1h","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"idempotency_claim|idempotency_complete|idempotency_get|Idempotency|request_hash|pending|claimed|complete","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","include":"*.py"},"output":"Found 79 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py:\n  Line 53:     IdempotencyResponse,\n\n  Line 695:                     Memory.status.in_((\"active\", \"confirmed\", \"pending\")),\n\n  Line 723:         \"\"\"Insert a new ``dedup_reviews`` row in ``pending`` status.\n\n  Line 765:         status: str = \"pending\",\n\n  Line 769:         newest-first. Default ``status='pending'`` keeps the busy-queue\n\n  Line 787:         \"\"\"Transition a review from ``pending`` to one of the terminal\n\n  Line 793:         if status not in DEDUP_REVIEW_STATUSES or status == \"pending\":\n\n  Line 1470:                     Memory.status.in_((\"active\", \"confirmed\", \"pending\")),\n\n  Line 1477:                 status_filter = Memory.status.in_((\"active\", \"confirmed\", \"pending\"))\n\n  Line 1519:                 Memory.status.in_((\"active\", \"confirmed\", \"pending\")),\n\n  Line 1552:                     Memory.status.in_((\"active\", \"confirmed\", \"pending\")),\n\n  Line 3467:         other pending writes in the same session) and forced\n\n  Line 4136:     async def fleet_get_pending_commands(\n\n  Line 4146:                     FleetCommand.status == \"pending\",\n\n  Line 4290:         \"\"\"I