t routes through the storage layer's ``metadata_patch``\n\n  Line 2364:     # synthetic key (single top-level JSONB ``||`` merge — note: not\n\n  Line 2369:     # ``None`` as ``\"merge\"`` here so SDK clients that serialise with\n\n  Line 2372:     # ``{\"metadata\": null}`` in merge mode raises 400 rather than\n\n  Line 2378:         effective_mode = data.metadata_mode or \"merge\"\n\n  Line 2401:                     \"metadata=null has no effect in merge mode; \"\n\n  Line 2406:             # Top-level JSONB ``||`` merge at the storage layer.\n\n  Line 2407:             # Nested objects are replaced, not recursively merged.\n\n  Line 2412:                 \"mode\": \"merge\",\n\n  Line 2414:             patch[\"metadata_patch\"] = data.metadata\n\n  Line 2415:         # else (empty dict in merge mode) → storage no-op, no audit\n\n  Line 2435:     # merge-mode patches from contributing to ``patch`` / ``changes``;\n\n  Line 2561:     Two behavioural details are preserved across the share:\n\n  Line 2580:     tokens = extract_entity_tokens(query, preserve_case=True)\n","metadata":{"matches":28,"truncated":false},"title":"agent_provided_enrichment_fields|update_memory_enrichment|metadata_patch|merge|agent_provided_fields|enrichment_pending|manual|preserve","time":{"start":1780728908437,"end":1780728908443}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04eb243c6a8c0fa1016a23c44c558481918b6ef3055d8c5107"}},"id":"prt_e9bb6ca8c0018vnEb5F1MZvkTD","sessionID":"ses_1644b0d23ffeX4h16ioztT6XB0","messageID":"msg_e9bb6a3f6001nzE41UFA2Ruh9Z"}}
